{"by": "rswail", "id": 43182656, "parent": 43181903, "text": "&gt;&gt; ... mainstream database <i>system</i> ...<p>&gt; SQLite, with far more installations than Postgres, isn&#x27;t a &quot;mainstream database&quot;?<p>It&#x27;s not a system, it&#x27;s a monolith library, which is why it is used wherever you want a local database with local storage.<p>Postgres implementations are a client&#x2F;server systems even if the connection is on localhost.<p>It&#x27;s also MVCC and has RLS and other requirements that do not necessarily apply to a local database like SQLite.<p>It&#x27;s not about the number of installations, it&#x27;s the type of database.", "time": 1740568247, "type": "comment"}